    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Unpaired Image-to-image Translation ",
        "text_level": 1,
        "bbox": [
            498,
            658,
            790,
            683
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "where $\\mathcal { F } ( p _ { 0 } , p _ { 1 } )$ are stochastic processes with marginals $\\pmb { p } _ { 0 }$ ， $_ { p _ { 1 } }$ at $t = 0$ and $t = 1$ ,respectively，while $W ^ { \\epsilon }$ isthe Wiener processwith variance∈,i.e.，given by the SDE: ",
        "bbox": [
            19,
            701,
            225,
            744
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "This problem has a unique solution,which is a diffusion process $\\tau ^ { * }$ described by the SDE: ",
        "bbox": [
            22,
            776,
            223,
            805
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "img_path": "/data/huangyc/Document2All/posterDataOutput_vlm/Light Schrödinger Bridge_poster/auto/images/equations/equations_4.jpg",
        "text": "$$\nW ^ { \\epsilon } : \\quad d X _ { t } = { \\sqrt { \\epsilon } } d W _ { t } .\n$$",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "bbox": [
            82,
            751,
            163,
            767
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "img_path": "/data/huangyc/Document2All/posterDataOutput_vlm/Light Schrödinger Bridge_poster/auto/images/equations/equations_5.jpg",
        "text": "$$\nT ^ { * } : \\quad d X _ { t } = g ^ { * } ( X _ { t } , t ) d t + \\sqrt { \\epsilon } d W _ { t } .\n$$",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "bbox": [
            59,
            812,
            186,
            829
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "image",
        "img_path": "/data/huangyc/Document2All/posterDataOutput_vlm/Light Schrödinger Bridge_poster/auto/images/images/fig_8.jpg",
        "image_caption": [],
        "image_footnote": [],
        "bbox": [
            27,
            841,
            205,
            941
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The minimizer T\\* is called the Schrodinger Bridge. ",
        "bbox": [
            51,
            951,
            181,
            979
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "img_path": "/data/huangyc/Document2All/posterDataOutput_vlm/Light Schrödinger Bridge_poster/auto/images/equations/equations_6.jpg",
        "text": "$$\n\\begin{array} { r } { \\pmb { g } ^ { * } ( x , t ) = \\epsilon \\nabla _ { x } \\log \\displaystyle \\int _ { \\mathbb R ^ { D } } \\mathcal { N } ( x ^ { \\prime } | x , ( 1 - t ) \\epsilon I _ { D } ) \\phi ^ { * } ( x ^ { \\prime } ) d x ^ { \\prime } } \\end{array}\n$$",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "bbox": [
            259,
            693,
            443,
            729
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Inourwork，we introduce (for convenience） the adjusted Schrodinger bridge potential $\\begin{array} { r } { v ^ { * } ( x _ { 1 } ) \\stackrel { \\mathrm { d e f } } { = } \\exp ( - \\frac { \\| x _ { 1 } \\| ^ { 2 } } { 2 \\epsilon } ) \\phi ^ { * } ( x _ { 1 } ) } \\end{array}$ ",
        "bbox": [
            249,
            735,
            454,
            768
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "3. Integration of the Schrodinger Bridge SDE. The Schrodinger bridge SDE: ",
        "bbox": [
            249,
            785,
            435,
            816
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "img_path": "/data/huangyc/Document2All/posterDataOutput_vlm/Light Schrödinger Bridge_poster/auto/images/equations/equations_7.jpg",
        "text": "$$\nT ^ { * } : \\quad d X _ { t } = g ^ { * } ( X _ { t } , t ) d t + \\sqrt { \\epsilon } d W _ { t } .\n$$",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "bbox": [
            288,
            822,
            415,
            839
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "admits a closed-form solution $\\pi ^ { * } ( x _ { 1 } | x _ { 0 } )$ expressed through theadjusted Schrodinger potential $v ^ { * }$ ： ",
        "bbox": [
            250,
            847,
            455,
            876
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "img_path": "/data/huangyc/Document2All/posterDataOutput_vlm/Light Schrödinger Bridge_poster/auto/images/equations/equations_8.jpg",
        "text": "$$\n\\pi ^ { * } ( x _ { 1 } | x _ { 0 } ) \\ { \\stackrel { \\mathrm { d e f } } { = } } \\ { \\frac { \\exp \\left( \\left. x _ { 0 } , x _ { 1 } \\right. / \\epsilon \\right) v ^ { * } ( x _ { 1 } ) } { c ^ { * } ( x _ { 0 } ) } } ,\n$$",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "bbox": [
            287,
            880,
            414,
            917
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "where $\\begin{array} { r } { c ^ { * } ( x _ { 0 } ) \\ { \\stackrel { \\mathrm { d e f } } { = } } \\ \\int _ { \\mathbb { R } ^ { D } } \\exp \\left( \\langle x _ { 0 } , x _ { 1 } \\rangle / \\epsilon \\right) v ^ { * } ( x _ { 1 } ) d x _ { 1 } } \\end{array}$ is the normalizing constant. ",
        "bbox": [
            250,
            925,
            453,
            958
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Qualitative results of our solver for   \nsolving the domain   \ntranslation problem   \n(in the latent space of the ALAE autoencoder). ",
        "bbox": [
            485,
            736,
            593,
            869
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Imagesresolution is 1024×1024. ",
        "bbox": [
            491,
            888,
            591,
            925
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
